Hello. I find myself very often doing stuff like this:

```
position += velocity * delta;
```

LibGDX currently makes this very bulky. There's no way to scale and add velocity to position without using a temporary Vector3 or modifying velocity permanently:

```
1. position.add(temp.set(velocity).scl(delta)); //Temporary vector!
2. position.add(velocity.scl(delta)); //Permanently modifies velocity!
```

The only "sane" option is manually doing it:

```
position.x += velocity.x * delta;
position.y += velocity.y * delta;
position.z += velocity.z * delta;
```

This is a very common operation, so adding a function for multiply-and-add (often abbreviated "mad") would be extremely convenient in this case:

```
position.mad(velocity, delta); //= position += velocity*delta
```

Implementation:

```
public void mad(Vector3 add, float scale){
    x += add.x * scale;
    y += add.y * scale;
    z += add.z * scale;
}
```

Adding ModelLoader.ModelParameters to support TextureParameter, MipMapping and Filtering. Please note that all these settings are the same for all model textures (in case it has several). Also my patch does not check if the selected texture format is compatible with transparent materials if any.

After the path one could set the desired parameters prior to call assetManager.load, like
        ModelLoader.ModelParameters mp = new ModelLoader.ModelParameters();
        mp.textureParameter.genMipMaps = true;
        mp.textureParameter.format = Pixmap.Format.RGB565;
        mp.textureParameter.minFilter = Texture.TextureFilter.MipMapLinearNearest;
        mp.textureParameter.magFilter = Texture.TextureFilter.Linear;
        assetManager.load("model.g3db", Model.class, mp);

Or even we can set such parameters as default in ModelParameters constructor if one wish.
